# qa-7th vscode SEV-2 regression — standard mode Ctrl+L selects the
# WHOLE current line, not just line_start..cursor. Previously was
# using SelectLine (vim V semantics) which left cursor in place;
# now uses SelectLineToEnd which moves cursor to line_end+1.

write notes.txt "hello world\nsecond line\n"
open notes.txt

# Cursor lands at start; move it into the middle of line 1.
key right
key right
key right
key right
key right

# Ctrl+L — should select the whole line, not just the 5 chars before.
key ctrl+l

# The status chip shows the selection length. With SelectLineToEnd
# the selection covers 'hello world\n' = 12 cells. SelectLine would
# have shown just 5.
# The status pane reflects selection state; verify via screen contains.
# (Statusline shows "Sel N" when there's an active selection.)
expect screen contains "Sel "
expect screen lacks "Sel 5 "
